1
00:00:02,396 --> 00:00:09,843
Here there was a plaque that mentioned its construction date in 2009

2
00:00:09,868 --> 00:00:12,917
This was part of the reconstruction that happened in 2009

3
00:00:12,942 --> 00:00:18,307
It is clear that modern marble was used and this building style

4
00:00:18,332 --> 00:00:23,411
In 2009 the church was renovated and...

5
00:00:23,436 --> 00:00:25,495
Additional annexes were added to it

6
00:00:25,599 --> 00:00:28,177
This hall used to be spacious

7
00:00:28,411 --> 00:00:34,713
Here the priest would sit at the head of the hall

8
00:00:34,738 --> 00:00:41,015
And there were seats arranged for the parishioners

9
00:00:41,040 --> 00:00:45,667
Even after Mass on Sundays

10
00:00:45,692 --> 00:00:48,870
The parishioners gathered and shared their concerns

11
00:00:48,895 --> 00:00:54,365
And discussed many matters related to Mosul’s community at that time

12
00:00:54,390 --> 00:00:56,917
This was called the church hall

13
00:00:56,942 --> 00:01:00,667
And it hosted special celebrations, whether at Christmas

14
00:01:00,692 --> 00:01:03,219
And the distribution of gifts to children

15
00:01:03,244 --> 00:01:09,911
In addition to Easter when coffee and Armenian food were served

16
00:01:09,936 --> 00:01:12,204
Especially in this hall

17
00:01:12,229 --> 00:01:17,021
So that it would be a shared occasion and a gathering

18
00:01:17,766 --> 00:01:25,188
Interviewer: What was the shape of the hall, and its features?

19
00:01:25,213 --> 00:01:27,375
There were seats here

20
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:32,506
And in this place there was a chair

21
00:01:32,531 --> 00:01:35,396
Where the church priest would sit

22
00:01:35,421 --> 00:01:39,146
And all of this space had chairs around it

23
00:01:39,171 --> 00:01:44,875
And the members of the Armenian church gathered in this hall

24
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:50,187
Whether to meet officials for congratulations on January 6

25
00:01:50,212 --> 00:01:54,511
We welcomed well-wishers from figures in the local government

26
00:01:54,536 --> 00:01:56,073
And from other churches

27
00:01:56,098 --> 00:01:58,372
To congratulate on the holidays

28
00:01:58,397 --> 00:02:01,810
And to exchange greetings on this occasion
